modules.description: Provides asynchronous operations for uploading, downloading, and listing blobs in Azure Storage, using async I/O and event loops. Works with byte sequences, file paths, and Azure blob container references. Enables efficient cloud storage integration in real-time data processing pipelines and distributed systems.

Generates signed HTTP requests for Azure Blob Storage operations, computes body lengths for different data formats, and performs asynchronous upload, download, append, and deletion of blobs. Works with HTTP methods, headers, URIs, and blob content represented as strings or bodies. Used to interact with Azure Blob Storage in real-time applications requiring secure, asynchronous data handling.
